Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and intercept navigation:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the async confirmation
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () =>
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");

                if (leave)
                    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            });

            return true; // Cancel the default back navigation
        }

        return false; // Allow normal navigation
    }
}
```

**2. Custom "Cancel" back button in the toolbar:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>
</ContentPage>
```

Or inline:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                        Command="{Binding CancelCommand}"
                        IconOverride="" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

**3. The ViewModel command:**

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
private async Task Cancel()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return;
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **hardware/gesture** back (Android back button, swipe).
- `Shell.BackButtonBehavior` controls the **toolbar** back button appearance and tap behavior.
- You need both to fully cover back navigation. The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the default navigation, so you must call `GoToAsync("..")` yourself when allowing it.
